{"TopicId":215752,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Bring back the maneuver node from before the first patch","CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-22T20:24:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-22T20:24:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if I\u0027m the odd one here, but I think the old maneuver node was better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile the new one seems to be more usable (and even that is debatable), it\u0027s less aesthetically pleasing, seems unfinished and resemble a dev tool (also it\u0027s too aliased):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#2e3035;color:#ffffff;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222YpzMah.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002233.82\u0022 height=\u0022254\u0022 width=\u0022751\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/2YpzMah.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe old one was, in my opinion, better at least from an artistic view. The only downside that I can see is that icons (prograde, retrograde...) were too small (and maybe the arrow needed to be a bit smaller, but not as small as the new one):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#2e3035;color:#ffffff;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tD37Fy2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002274.32\u0022 height=\u0022136\u0022 width=\u0022183\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/tD37Fy2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-22T20:28:24Z\u0022 title=\u002203/22/2023 08:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EProperly embedded pictures\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-22T23:54:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunction over form in UI. New one is definitely more clear to use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T02:44:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll respect to the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, no.\u00A0 God, no.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis version works.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sea_Kerman","CreatedById":226149,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T06:56:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah this version is much less fiddly to use\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LameLefty","CreatedById":57336,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T12:03:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, please for the love of the Kraken, just \u2026 no.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T12:11:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say that both iterations are equally bad in how they fail to deliver an actually *good* maneuver editing and planning tool.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI will see myself out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T12:36:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224264366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679573501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gotmachine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Gotmachine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nboth iterations are equally bad\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first was terrible.\u00A0 This one works.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people want more out it - but that is not \u0027equally bad\u0027\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFWIW allow me to remind:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/lq2uIa2Sg0I?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 EA Maneuver NOPE.  This is what frustrates me.\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe complaints of the current version seem to be about aliasing and refinement\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShrug\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-23T12:37:45Z\u0022 title=\u002203/23/2023 12:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T12:50:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E but I disagree completely\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new UI is SO much better than the older v0.1.0.0 UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tapeta","CreatedById":196184,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T13:08:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew system is better, because on the new one I can clearly see what is prograde, what is retrograde, normal, antinormal ... . That was not the case of old pre-patch style.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T20:50:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy playing around a bit more with it, I changed my mind, the new one is a lot easier to use than the previous one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still find the last one better looking than what we have now but as The Aziz says\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224264164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679529282\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/23/2023 at 12:54 AM, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunction over form in UI. New one is definitely more clear to use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile it\u0027s better it\u0027s not perfect as the center is still tricky to grab sometimes (especially when you scrolled far away from the node)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}